
# Offensive Security

## Introduction

Offensive Security is the practice of identifying and exploiting vulnerabilities in systems, networks, and applications to understand how attackers operate.

The goal of offensive security is not to cause harm but to discover weaknesses before malicious attackers can exploit them.

Security professionals use offensive security techniques to improve the overall security posture of organizations.

